{
  "text": "In this study, uncertainty was rated relatively high, which is consistent with prior studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Interestingly, the students in our study scored personal relevance lowest, which is contrary to the findings of [CITATION_5] , [CITATION_6] and [CITATION_7] , but consistent with the findings of [CITATION_8] . These differences could be attributed to the differences in educational contexts (secondary versus higher education). University students are often older and therefore could be more conscious and more realistic about their perceptions of their learning environments compared with primary and secondary students. This could suggest the need for further studies of these variables in the context of higher education.",
